sentences: Elizabeth Eden Harris (born May 31, 1997), known professionally as Cupcakke (often stylized as cupcakKe; pronounced ), is an American rapper, songwriter and record producer from Chicago, Illinois.
Cupcakke began her career as a rapper by releasing material online in late 2012.
In 2015, two of her songs, "Deepthroat" and "Vagina", went viral on video-sharing platforms.
The songs were later included on her debut mixtape, Cum Cake (2016), which was included on Rolling Stone's list of the Best Rap Albums of 2016 at number 23.
